$ Windows: Language for Non-Unicode Programs

The *Language for Non-Unicode Programs*, prior to Windows XP known as *system locale*, specifies the default → Windows/development/code-page[code page].

A dialog that allows to change this language can be opened from → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe[cmd.exe] by executing `intl.cpl`.

